metadata.name: Tranquility #34
metadata.description:
There was an original meaning to this piece, but it washed away over time, nevertheless Tranquility is a representation of the challenges of connecting to others and the resilience required to navigate the complexity of human relationships. Tranquility features sharp and dynamic lines that result in intricate and often chaotic patterns (conveying the intensity and complexity of the human experience).

Generative artwork - www.petitsapin.com
Press "s" in live view to download high-res version.

metadata.name: Fermi Paradox #4
metadata.description:
Speculation regarding the UFO phenomenon have been going on around the world for quite sometime now. At the same time, as humanity as a collective is making some progress towards the exploration of outer space. However, the question "Are we all alone?" is still unanswered!

Fermi Paradox came from the speculative idea of the UFO phenomenon being some sort of galactic watchers sent by aliens to keep tabs on other intelligent life forms. This is a generative art project representing the watchers and the spaces being watched.

This project takes forward the idea of a digital diorama inspired by holographic dreams of our collective past, putting the viewers in place of the aliens, gazing upon different planets as the watchers go out exploring the universe.

- 16 Terrains/Landscapes
- 6 UFO Variations
- 1000 color variations
- Alien Day and Night Cycles

All generated with code via the webgl platform cables.gl.

!!Might be a bit heavy on your system!!
- Hold 'P' to check performance
- Click 'S' to save a screenshot

metadata.name: RULES (for Elementary Cellular Automata) #7
metadata.description:
An important element of generative art is emergence. The most famous algorithm for this is probably Cellular Automata (CA).

However, numerous generative artists have created works using CA, which has lost its visual freshness and is like chewing gum that has lost its taste.

Although it is such a classic algorithm, adding my own little ideas to it and finding a new "flavor" is the reason why I code.

Here, the subject is 1D Elementary Cellular Automata, the simplest of all cellular automata. 1D Elementary Cellular Automata has 256 different rules, which change the shapes produced. This work aims to create more complex shapes by randomly selecting some of those rules and placing multiple of them on the screen.

The on/off of the CA cell is often likened to the behavior of living creatures.As of 2022, in the country where I live, prices are rising, wages are not increasing, and COVID-19 has not yet ended. I created this work with the image of people at the mercy of these various rules.

---

Screen click: Change rules
S key: Save png
L key: Show/hide grid

metadata.name: monogrid 1.1 CE #195
metadata.description:
Each monogrid artwork gets initialized with a start up algorithm that builds up a set of rectangles and fills them with pixels. There are two different styles, 'Pixel' and 'Line', to create the initial image.

There is a set of 16 animations at work. 4 noise based animations, 4 shifting animations, 4 modulo based animation and 4 reset animations, all run in parallel. Each animation selects a rectangle from the initial setup and edits the pixels in this area. The selection process runs independently and animations can overlap which results in a new style of animation.

monogrid 1.1 is based on the original series at https://monogrid.xyz, but there are no black/white versions included. The color palette is a mixture of one of 12 colors plus black or white.
The fragment shader has been updated in the way the 16 different animations get summed up. This version would appear more chaotic and organic.

monogrid 1.1 - Collectors Edition
Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: tratti #229
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

----

metadata.name: ASSEMBLING MACHINE #242
metadata.description:
The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.
---------------
Collectors at the highest tier (125 tez) may claim a signed 8”x10” print of their mint. Please look for details about prints on Twitter (@teaboswell), or contact me directly
---------------
CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines
B - Cycle border sizes (0 -> 100 -> 200 -> 300px)

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
